Cabinet ministers responsible for safety and justice will outline their plans for the 21-day nationwide lockdown. They are expected to tell the nation what their respective departments will be doing to enforce regulations. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - An Inter-Ministerial Committee responsible for safety and justice will outline their plans for the 21-day nationwide lockdown on Wednesday. Cabinet ministers are expected to tell the nation what their respective departments will be doing to enforce regulations. South Africa will be on lockdown from Thursday evening. The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has climbed to 709. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 